(38, 'Apple', 'Apples are nutritious and provide several health benefits:', 'here are thousands of apple varieties, with some of the most popular including:\r\n\r\nFuji: Sweet and juicy, great for eating raw.\r\nGranny Smith: Tart and crisp, ideal for baking.\r\nGala: Mildly sweet and fragrant, perfect for snacking.\r\nHoneycrisp: Known for its balance of sweetness and tartness, with an excellent crunch.\r\nNutritional Benefits\r\nApples are nutritious and provide several health benefits:\r\n\r\nLow in Calories: A medium apple has about 95 calories.\r\nFiber: Good source of dietary fiber, which aids digestion.\r\nVitamins: Rich in vitamin C and various antioxidants.\r\nHeart Health: May help reduce the risk of heart disease due to their high fiber and antioxidant content.\r\nGrowing Conditions\r\nClimate: Apples thrive in temperate climates.\r\nSoil: Well-drained, loamy soil is ideal.\r\nPollination: Most apple varieties require cross-pollination for optimal fruit production.\r\nCulinary Uses\r\nRaw: Eaten fresh, sliced, or in salads.\r\nBaking: Commonly used in pies, crisps, and cakes.\r\nSauces and Ciders: Made into applesauce or fermented into hard cider.\r\nStorage\r\nStore apples in a cool, dry place', 'top-selling', 'fruits', 'istockphoto-1214421019-612x612.jpg', 3000, '5'),
